com.informix.jdbc

Interface IfxProtocol

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    IfxSqli, IfxXASqli

    public interface IfxProtocol

    IfxProtocol represents the protocol and data exchange between the client and an Informix database server. It sends and processes the messages and the data flow between the client and server.

    See Also:
    Connection, ResultSet

      • getaRow

        boolean getaRow(int direction,
              int count,
              int scrolltype,
              int isscrollcurs,
              java.sql.Statement stmt)
                throws java.sql.SQLException
        Move the cursor from the current position to +/- count depending on the direction specified. If direction is ResultSet.FETCH_FORWARD, then advance the current position to current + count. If direction is ResultSet.FETCH_REVERSE, then move the current position to current - count. FETCH_FORWARD/FETCH_REVERSE are from JDBC 2.0 support for scrollable cursors.
        Parameters:
        direction - Valid values are FETCH_FORWARD/FETCH_REVERSE. For JDBC 1.2, only FETCH_FORWARD is supported.
        count - number of rows to move forward/backward. For JDBC 1.2, count can only be set to 1.
        scrolltype - either absolute, relative, next, ... etc.
        isscrollcurs - - is it a scroll cursor ?
        stmt - - used eventually to see if the user is changing the return type of the data. See executeScrollFetch().
        Returns:
        true if a valid row is found, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException
